text: Hey there Liam, I’d recommend posting this in <#CBNDYJJAZ|jobs> to get better visibility from folks looking for projects like this. Wish ya good luck. If you don’t find someone in a timely manner I recommend checking out our <https://ecosystem.HubSpot.com/marketplace/solutions/website-development|solutions partners>
Hi everybody, i'm new in HubSpot :slightly_smiling_face:
Hi everyone, I'm new to the HubSpot Developers Slack. I've passed the CMS Developer and Implementation certifications so far. I hope to help out where and when I can.

If you're familiar with Node.js then it should be a breeze. Serverless functions are also only available to CMS Enterprise clients so double check that you have that. Check out the <https://developers.HubSpot.com/docs/cms/guides/getting-started-with-serverless-functions|HubSpot Developer Docs> regarding serverless functions.

You may have already figured it out by now, but there's some class name in your template CSS that's causing the blue background. Inspect element should help you figure out which class is causing you the headache.
